                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.00/390.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>President Arosemena assures me that he desires supervision of the elections to
                    the extent necessary to ensure fairness.</p>
                <p>A letter requesting supervision of registration by the United States has been
                    written to the President and sent to the Minister of Panama at Washington by the
                    Committee of the Patriotic Union. This supervision is desired as soon as
                    possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
